The paper proposes a new model of provenance for query evaluation, which is a topic in database systems (cs.DB). The model is based on game theory, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and also has connections to logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the relationship between game provenance and semiring provenance, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC). Overall, the paper's focus on database systems and game theory suggests that cs.DB and cs.GT are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.LO, and cs.CC.
